 LAFIA – Nasarawa State Chapter of Young Progressive Party ( YPP), Saturday applauded President Muhamadu Buhari for accented to the electoral act amendment bill into law. With this, the party said the young people can contest any political position and won it gallantly. We’re Making Progress In Immunisation, PHC System, Says Buhari I Look Forward To Being Ex-President Of Nigeria – Buhari Mr. Bishop Mathew, the chairman of Nasarawa State Chapter of Young Progressive Party (YPP), disclosed this while answering questions from Journalists in Lafia, the state capital. According to him,” I’m full of joy, we as a party are excited for this singular act that President Buhari did on Friday, Nigerians are happy. ” President Muhamadu Buhari has made another historical event in the history of Nigeria politics. People thought is not going to sign the bill. Buhari is truly a leader who wants the future of Nigerian politics to be great. He explained that President Muhamadu Buhari has created another avenue where youth can be a vote and be voted for in any position in the forthcoming general election in the country. The YPP Chairman also averred that before now, the conscience of youth was being bought off with money during an election; adding that with this amendment act the chance of young people winning the election is great in the next election in the state. POLL Mr. Mathew, further assured that with the accent of this bill young people can go for any position and win the seat in the forthcoming general election in Nasarawa state. He however called on the youths to actively participate in politics in order to contribute their own quota for the development of the state and country at large.